Minor: It would be better to move the dropStats check outside of the lambda. There's no need to check it inside when we could just use a different lambda that doesn't put a conditional inside a tight loop:
    if (dropStats()) {
      return CloseableIterable.transform(liveEntries(), e -> e.file().copyWithoutStats()).iterator();
    } else {
      return CloseableIterable.transform(liveEntries(), e -> e.file().copy()).iterator();
    }

